## Reflection

This project highlighted how easy it is for small syntax mistakes to create unexpected behaviour. Neither of the issues I encountered were particularly complex, but both required careful reading of the code to identify what had gone wrong.

One of the most valuable lessons was seeing how a missing variable reference and a single misplaced character in a `sed` command could completely change the output of an otherwise functional script. It reinforced the importance of checking assumptions and reviewing commands carefully when troubleshooting.

I was pleased that I completed the project with minimal assistance and also took the opportunity to improve the final product beyond the stated requirements. While the script works as intended, I can already see opportunities for improvement and optimisation, making this a project I would like to revisit in the future as my Bash scripting skills continue to develop.
